703903f-a.title: Brooklyn: Cropsey Avenue - Bay 26th Street
703903f-a.text:
Cropsey Ave., south side, on line of Bay 26th Street, showing the
Hotel Bensonhurst, no longer in existence. In 1890, the Bath Beach Hotel,
was on this site, and later it was enlarged and given the name of Hotel
Bensonhurst.
About 1900.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

703905f-a.title: Brooklyn: Cropsey Avenue - Bay 26th Street
703905f-a.text:

known in 1890 as the Bath Beach Hotel; at a later date it was extended and en-
larged and became the Hotel Bensonhurst. (It deees not appear on the 1929
Brooklyn atlas).
1925.
